      • drawDashedLine

        public static int drawDashedLine(java.awt.Graphics g,
                                 int xbeg,
                                 int ybeg,
                                 int xend,
                                 int yend,
                                 int dashLength,
                                 int dashSpace,
                                 int dashStart)
        Draws a dashed line and returns the length of undrawn dash. The returned undrawn length can be used as a dashStart for another call to drawDashedLine to keep dashes consistent between connected lines.
        Parameters:
        g - graphics context to draw to
        xbeg - beginning x position draw line at
        ybeg - beginning y position draw line at
        xend - ending x position draw line to
        yend - ending y position draw line to
        dashLength - length of solid part of dashed line
        dashSpace - length between solid parts of dashed line
        dashStart - length of first dash to draw
        Returns:
        remaining length not drawn of last dash drawn
